svg.text: Male,40 years old,Waiting for school children and work out near school gate,at 17:30subway: everyday-bring some newspaper.-chat with friends (more re-laxing.walk for 10 min directly to home.-willing to walk if time permit-ted.“My children don’t like to walk especially when weather is cold.”

Female, about 25 years old, writting e-mail with mobile-phone inside subway station,at 18:00SUBWAY: every day-always commute alone-use mobile phone for work or entertainment.WALK for 10 min directly to home.-walk is priority if weather is good (convenient&healthy“I never go to the park spend most time in home alone, Sometimes boring”

Female, about 20 years old, having dinner in Family Mart,at 18:30SUBWAY: once a week WALK for 20 min to dor-matry.-have dinner/ drink or go to shops on the way.-walk alone so quickly.-walk with friends more re-laxed.“I want to spend more time outside when weath-er is good but no appro-priate place.”

Male, 43 years old, hurrying home from subway station.at 19:00SUBWAT: always-subway station near home so it’s convenient.-subway have a accurate schedule.WALK for 5-10 min directly to home.-family member buy vegeta-bles for meal in the after-noon.“Commuting is so tiring, so after finishing dinner we go to bed early.”

Female, 42 years old, going out from subway exit.at 19:20SUBWAT: not often-work place near home, sometimes take bus.WALK directly to home.-or buy some condiment on the way home“My husband and son both have dinner near their work place or subway station in-dividually”
